<br>
thanks for the translation, isharra!<br>
<br>
as for fictitious languages...personally, any language that was created by one person, or formed at one particular time especially to benefit or enhance a work of literature is probably going to be fictitious.  it never evolved from real humans going about their business in the natural world, as modern english has from proto-indo-european or whatever.  also, it isn't spoken on a daily basis by a community, other than some kind of small social club as is qenya, drow, and so forth.<br>
<br>
they're kinda like dead languages, but made up instead of having any kind of historical basis in being used by a real live human community.  then again, this is all a personal classification, and i'm definitely no linguist.  i'd be very interested to know what a 'real' linguist would think of them, though.<br>
<br>
a few tips:   a)&quot;imaginary&quot; and &quot;fictitious&quot; weren't being used to dismiss it out of hand as any way less valid.  my message would've been similar if the person had written this note in sanskrit.  b)it was apparently not of tolkienien origin.  at least if it had been, i'd have known where to look to make a rough translation.  c)some folks need to lighten up, and stop putting words and ideas in everyone else's mouth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugravesfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graves FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 2:13:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2521.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abbils... above jal else...Xathari</span><hr size=1> Just another example of Bertoxxulous' disease at work.  In this case, an obvious case of Feeble Mind.<br>
