</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 9:43:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2521.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abbils... above jal else...Xathari</span><hr size=1> I dislike the casual usage of Drow language, especially when only one or two words are used in a sentence. I put it in the same boat I do someone saying &quot;you are so baka&quot; or &quot;hola, how are you?&quot; If you want to speak Japanese or Spanish, speak Japanese or Spanish; don't just throw a word in.<br>
<br>
It makes it seem like you're either trying to make yourself sound superior to the person you're talking with (as in, &quot;Ha ha! I know a language that you don't!&quot;), or that you're just too lazy to translate more than a handful of words.<br>
<br>
I guess this is just one of those things that won't change, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTB phat newt</span><br>  Posts: 678<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 10:49:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2521.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abbils... above jal else...Xathari</span><hr size=1> With, say, Tolkein's elvish, I would agree.  With Drow however, the language is so incomplete that chances are you CAN'T say a complete sentence in it.  Hell, I couldn't even find a complete conjugation for &quot;to be&quot; or &quot;to have&quot; when I went looking.  It's just ... not a whole language. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 10:53:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2521.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abbils... above jal else...Xathari</span><hr size=1> Oh, all right. I was under the impression there was a comprehensive dictionary out there somewhere, instead of the fractured and unfinished one you described. Oh well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span 